cff-version: 1.2.0
title: "Methodology-as-Infrastructure: From Framework to Runtime"
message: "If you use this work, please cite it using the metadata from this file."
type: software
authors:
  - family-names: Shatny
    given-names: Michael
    orcid: "https://orcid.org/0009-0006-2011-3258"
doi: "10.5281/zenodo.18946630"
repository-code: "https://github.com/semanticintent/methodology-as-infrastructure"
url: "https://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.18946630"
abstract: >-
  Methodology-as-Infrastructure proposes that analytical methodologies can be
  compiled into deterministic execution layers — transforming descriptive
  frameworks into executable runtime infrastructure. Using CAL (Cascade Analysis
  Language) as the primary case study, this paper demonstrates how a 6-dimensional
  cascade analysis methodology was encoded into a domain-specific language with
  12 keywords, 3 formulas, and a PEG parser, producing a six-stage deterministic
  pipeline (Sense → Analyze → Measure → Decide → Act → Validate) that operates
  across domains without modification. 239 cross-industry case studies across
  148+ sectors validate the approach. The concept extends the "as-a-Service" and
  "as-Code" paradigms into a new category: methodology that becomes the
  infrastructure other systems build upon. v1.1 adds Appendix B: the citation
  chain across the MaI ecosystem. v1.2 updates the evidence base (239 cases,
  148+ sectors), adds WATCH and RECALL keywords (12 total), extends the pipeline
  to six stages (Validate added), and adds the Intent-as-Infrastructure paper
  (DOI: 10.5281/zenodo.20681523) to the Appendix B citation chain.
keywords:
